channel.title: Project... IDK
channel.description:
It's not really called Project IDK btw, i just haven't though of a name so far, lol.
It was originally PKScapeX, but that name defeated the point of it not just being a pk server, then i moved onto RuneIsle, but that name fails imo, so i'm currently thinking up a name now, and if you have any suggestions for a name please post it.
I have not worked yet on many in-game features but here are some pictures of the actual server itself (to give you some ideas);
[IMG]http://img378.imageshack.us/img378/9417/19608740vm2.png[/img]
[IMG]http://img378.imageshack.us/img378/5876/91393394ho6.png[/img]
[IMG]http://img378.imageshack.us/img378/4732/47965893nz0.png[/img]
[IMG]http://img183.imageshack.us/img183/5884/79064870rd1.png[/img]
[IMG]http://img183.imageshack.us/img183/5488/52393858jv1.png[/img]
[IMG]http://img183.imageshack.us/img183/2489/42230621el6.png[/img]
[IMG]http://img183.imageshack.us/img183/1515/54750332fx9.png[/img]
I have several features done at the minute:
[ul][*]Full specials with perfect timers. [*]Attack timers based 100% from RuneScape's knowledge base. [*]Dueling/Staking (Fully handled). [*]Half of desert treasure quest done. [*]Agility with walking over obstacles etc (Not the tutorial one, made it 100% myself). [*]Main methods and skills etc seperated into their own classes. [*]Very nice PvP system basically identical to the old RuneScape. [*]Stable and efficient root file. [*]Several packets are processed in their own classes. [*]MySQL combatible. [*]Very clean programming, tryed following code conventions as much as possible. [*]Many methods rewritten and cleaned up, still to do loading and saving. [*]Perfect wilderness levels. [*]Perfect wilderness single zones, 100% flawless identical to RuneScape, didn't follow any tutorial and was one of the first, if not the first to make it, i still don't think anyone has it the same as RuneScape like i do with perfect timers and messages etc. [*]All three melee forms take effect on the wilderness levels and single combat zones. [*]Many more features not listed.[/ul]
Still to do:
[ul][*]Complete the rest of the skills. [*]Finish perfect slayer. [*]Add npc's around the map. [*]Add alot more areas so the game doesn't revolve around one or two main citys, i want to use up as much of the map as possible. [*]Rewrite player loading and saving to make it much for efficient, this will prevent all resets etc because of how poorly it is currently programmed. [*]Rewrite ALL of the main methods fully following code conventions and clean programming and spacing. [*]Make sure every piece of programming is efficient and adds the least amount of size to the file as possible. [*]Finish my half programmed minigames such as castle wars and pest control. [*]Enable the server to integrate with vBulletin forum, tryed before but the MySQL connection failed after like three connections, so although i'm good with MySQL in PHP i need to practise with MySQL in Java. [*]Add ways of getting around such as boats etc, rather than portals. [*]Program all magic spells to perfection. [*]Rewrite the max hit formula. [*]Form an economy so items are not 'easy' to get but are fairly hard. [*]Think of a catchy name for the server.[/ul]
There is alot more to do, and it will all get done.
I need a few programmers and programming assistants, and also a client programmer. [B] Requirements:[/B]
Programmers; Server programmers must have a fair knowledge in private servers, and of course java. I would prefer to see some examples of YOUR work, and i must obviously not hate you or anything like that.
Programming assistants; Programming assistants will help with stuff which requires hardly any knowledge except simple english and probably maths, this would involve such activitys such as ordering things, removing things from certain pieces of programming, basic stuff really.
Client programmers; Client programmers should have substantial knowledge in client programming. You would need to follow requests from me to fulfill what i want putting into the client. I am only accepting fairly good client programmers with proof of work, or people i know can do a good job at client programming. [B] Please note[/B] - None of the staff will recieve a full copy of the server, mainly for the fact that i've spent months on end programming it up to this point and there's no way i'm going to take the risk of it being released to the public or claimed as someone elses work, i've learnt to never fully trust anyone on the internet.
That's about it really, if you're interested, leave a post, or if it's private, pm me.
If you have any suggestions for in-game features, or especially a server name, post with that suggestions.
I would also like supportive posts only, no flaming etc, because only jealous people flame against projects with no reason.
Thanks.
